Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
check_bus_guides(25.10)                                check_bus_guides(25.10)

Name
       check_bus_guides  -  Checks  bus  guides  for violations during master-
       clone-aware net group implementation flow

Syntax
       check_bus_guides

       [-help]

       [-net_groups <list_of_net_groups>]

       [-outFile <file_name>]

       Checks bus guides for violations during  master-clone-aware  net  group
       implementation  flow.  It  checks for the consistency of net groups and
       bus guides by performing the following:

              * Bus-guide physical checks:

                *
                   Reports over-drawn bus guides.

                * Reports under-drawn bus guides (bus guide does not reach the
                  sink of net group).

                * Reports bus guide  that  do  not  overlap/connect  with  the
                  source of net group.

              * Checks  the  net-group consistency and reports non-homogeneous
                nets in a net group.

       Note: The check_bus_guides command does not support nested designs yet.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each check_bus_guides parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man check_bus_guides

       -net_groups <list_of_net_groups>
              Specifies the net groups whose bus guides are to be checked.

              Default : *.

              Example:

              # -net_groups {ng1 ng2 ng3-*} (string, optional)

              Data_type: string, optional

       -outFile <file_name>
              Specifies the name of the file where the bus guide violation log
              is stored.

              Default: checkBg.rpt

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The following command checks the bus guides for violations.

                check_bus_guides

              * The following command checks the bus guides of net groups ng1,
                ng2, and ng3 for violations.

                check_bus_guides -net_groups {ng1 ng2 ng3}

Related Information
              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

